      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The cycle repeats with a predictable pattern of flats and sharps thanks to the whole-tone step movement around the wheel. Starting from C major, moving down a perfect fifth ($\\text{C} \\rightarrow \\text{F}$) adds one flat, making it F major/minor. Keeping that pattern, $\\text{F} \\rightarrow \\text{Bb}$ adds a second flat, and so on, until you cycle all the way back to $\\text{C}$ major, completing the loop. Think of it like a chain: you add one sharp moving up—$\\text{G} \\rightarrow \\text{D} \\rightarrow \\text{A}$, and one flat moving down—$\\text{F} \\rightarrow \\text{Bb} \\rightarrow \\text{Eb}$.",
